(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - Namibian media say an elephant trampled and killed an Argentine who was in a group of hunters tracking a herd of elephants.The Namibia Press Agency said the hunter, identified as 46-year-old Jose Monzalvez, was killed on Saturday afternoon in a private wildlife area 70km northwest of the small town of Kalkfeld.The agency said Monzalvez, who worked for an oil company, was with another Argentine and three Namibians when he was killed. It says one of the elephants charged before the group was able to find a spot to aim and shoot.The report says Monzalvez had a hunting permit with him and that relatives have been informed of his death.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.